  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - No marketing evidence has been submitted to demonstrate, over a period of 18 months, that there is no longer a need or demand for the Commercial Class E use, given that the application site is located within a designate shopping Local Centre. The proposal has not demonstrated compliance with Policy LP44(1)(a) of the 2023 Wandsworth Local Plan, and the principle of development would be unacceptable.\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - By reason of its design, location, and internal arrangement, the development would fail to provide an acceptable standard of accommodation for future occupiers. The habitable rooms of Flats 1 and 3 would suffer from a poor level of privacy due to their direct relationship with Mitcham Lane. Additionally, Flats 2 and 4 are provided with inadequate outdoor amenity space, while Flats 1 and 3 lack any outdoor space altogether, are single aspect with little, or no opportunity for natural ventilation. As a result, the proposal is considered to offer a substandard level of accommodation for future occupiers and would therefore fail to comply with Policy LP27 of the Wandsworth Local Plan (2023) and Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021).",
    "Reason : 3 - In dealing with this application the Council has implemented the requirement in the National Planning Policy Framework, as far as practicable, sought solutions to problems arising in relation to dealing with the planning application. We have made available detailed advice in the form of our statutory policies in the Local Plan consisting of the Core Strategy, Development Management Policies Document, Supplementary Planning documents and where appropriate the Site Specific Allocations Document as well as offering a full pre application advice service. However, we have been unable to seek solutions to problems as the principle of the proposal is clearly contrary to our statutory policies and negotiation could not overcome the reasons for refusal."
